sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: Roman DBDR Acquisition Corp. II SEC 10-Q Report
feed.summary: Roman DBDR Acquisition Corp. II (DRDB), a blank check company, has released its 10-Q report for the quarter ended September 30, 2025. The report details net income of $2.14 million for the quarter and $6.38 million for the nine months, derived from interest on Trust Account investments. The company is actively searching for a business combination target in cybersecurity, AI, or fintech sectors, with a deadline of December 16, 2026, and acknowledges liquidity concerns for sustaining operations.
